description: Plural of custom. Perhaps influenced by or taken as a corruption of customhouse, from Middle English custome hous.

entries.meaning: (in the plural) The duties or taxes imposed on imported or exported goods.
examples: Customs of Â£200 were due on all the wine we took back from France.

entries.meaning: (in the singular or uncountable) The government department or agency that is authorised to collect the taxes imposed on imported goods.
examples: Customs stopped us in the airport for an inspection.

entries.meaning: The process of going through customs checks at a border checkpoint.
examples: They usually don't care about customs, but she was clearly planning on selling most of it.

entries.meaning: The location at a border checkpoint where customs checks are carried out.

description: See the etymology of the corresponding lemma form.
